post_text: We are excited to announce that our application to continue the Summer Food Service Program has been approved by KSDE. Effective Sept. 8, all USD 392 students will receive free breakfast and lunch meals. The length of time we are able to offer this service will be determined by available Federal Funding and actions by Congress, but is currently authorized through December, 2020. We will notify parents in a timely manner when we have to move back to charging for meals.

post_text: OHS FFA is seeking donations to aid Hurricane Laura victims. Can you help?
shared_text:
Osborne County Ag & FFA
September 3 at 10:44 AM ·

If you've ever been part of FFA, or even agriculture, you know we stick together and help each other out no matter what. The Osborne County FFA Chapter is now collecting items that will be sent to FFA Chapters in Louisiana who were impacted by Hurricane Laura.

Donations can be dropped off at the High School between 7:30am and 4:00pm. Our collection will run from September 4th to September 18th.

Please contact Mrs. Kuhlmann if you have any questions.
akuhlmann@usd392.com

post_text:
Guidelines implemented at Osborne High School Volleyball and Football games due to COVID-19. Remember the following rules are to help keep our athletes and communities safe.

VOLLEYBALL
-Wear masks and social distance at all times
-Wash hands on a regular basis
-Sit in designated areas for your team
-Do not touch the game ball if it comes into the stands, a player will get it
-Wait outside after the games for your athlete

FOOTBALL
-Wear masks when entering and paying at the field
-Wear masks when going into the restrooms, at the concession stand and while in the stadium or bleachers
-Social distance while in the stands or standing around the fence area
-Stay off the football field at all times

Thank you for your cooperation with these guidelines. Also, please remember each school has their own rules which we will need to follow. All will be requiring masks so keep some available.

shared_text:
Arika Kuhlmann is with Angela Befort.
August 25 at 4:04 PM ·

We had an exciting day in Room 204.

• The Biology classes tested whether or not double stuffed Oreos are actually double stuffed to practice using the scientific method. Many groups found their cookies were more than double stuffed, with only one group finding theirs weren’t double stuffed at all. 🥛

• The Animal Science class practiced their livestock terminology with a few games of Spoons. We ended the period with an all class round. 🐂

• Not pictured: the skink that appeared out of nowhere and decided to join the Plant and Soil Science class. 🦎

post_text:
A note from Cross Country Coaches Adam and Ashley Bedient:

We are extremely excited to announce the establishment of a Junior High Cross Country program at Osborne! Thank you very much to the school board members, the faculty and staff of USD 392, and the friends and relatives who helped to get this accomplished. Anyone who is interested in joining or would simply like more information, please contact Adam and Ashley Bedient (thebeedos@hotmail.com). We would especially like to encourage “non-runners” and people who believe they “aren’t fast enough” to please reach out. Several of our current and past runners once claimed the same thing! Also, there will be a team run tonight (Tuesday, July 14th) @ 8:00pm. Meet at the Northeast side of the ballfields. Go Bulldogs!
